OL,3,CSon killed mother in her home while
OL,4,Cclaiming 'demons were responsible'
OL,6,FJones was found guilty following a
OL,7,Fnine-day trial at Portsmouth Crown
OL,8,FCourt. He is due to be sentenced in
OL,9,FJanuary 2025.
OL,11,FThe jury at Portsmouth Crown Court
OL,12,Fheard that Anarlyn Jones had called
OL,13,F999 and told the operator that he had
OL,14,Frepeatedly stabbed his mother, but
OL,15,Fthat she had begged him to do it and
OL,16,Fdemons were responsible, which he
OL,17,Frepeated to officers at the scene.
